content.description:
Climb the large right-facing ledge at the scoop directly above the small boulder. Unique movement.

A little mossy at the moment but it's a fun climb and might get some traffic if it were cleaner.
content.location: Directly uphill of the Metroid Prime boulder.

content.description: SDS. Climb the flat face of the elephant boulder by bear hugging either side of the face. Work your hands and feet up and topout.
content.location: On the elephant boulder in the East Forest. Same boulder as "Can you smell the gas".

climbs.name: Can you smell the gas (AKA Sore Thumb)

content.description: Sit start on jug and right pinch, move up using holds on either side of the arete.  Route finishes up and right on slopey holds.
content.protection: Crash Pad and a spotter would be nice.
content.location: Park in the east lot and walk back down the road ~10-15 feet till you pass a big boulder on the left, a trail starts from here and works up into the east forest.  Follow the trail (staying left) past some boulders (including Stinking Slopers)  till the trail becomes blocked by logs, step around the logs and look for a trail to your left.  Follow this trail to another group of boulders, the route is on the elephant boulder....hidden up and left out of view above a cool looking heel traverse line.
